On 4-May-04, at 7:44 PM, Paul Gould wrote:
> Sounds like you are expiring the random loss of amperage through old 
> wiring scenario.  Remember that there is a lot of wire between the 
> ignition switch to the starter and back.  A typical solution is to 
> install a WR-1 starter relay kit, or do what I did and grabbed a 
> standard hella 4 pole 30 amp relay and wired it between the starter 
> and and battery.  That way your key is only powering the relay which 
> is using a heavy gauge wire from the battery to the relay and starter. 
> Eliminated all of my random not starting problems.  You can google the 
> wr-1 relay and get the wiring procedures and diagram....
